    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This is a concours-level 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, featuring the iconic wide-body architecture and a 3.6L flat-six engine that exhibits perfect compression across all cylinders. The powerplant is mechanically flawless, having undergone a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a proactive water pump replacement to ensure cooling system integrity. The G96 six-speed manual transaxle offers surgical precision, delivering power through a fresh Sachs clutch to the all-wheel-drive system with zero drivetrain lash. The chassis is tightened with Bilstein PSS10 adjustable coilovers, while the braking system features refurbished Brembo monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors for optimal thermal dissipation. The paint-metered exterior is matched by a pristine undercarriage, free of any oxidation or fluid seepage. This is a turn-key masterpiece for the discerning purist who demands peak volumetric efficiency and structural integrity.",
